put.description:
Most users have a single GetGo account, but if the user has multiple GetGo accounts, there are limitations to your ability to make updates. Modification of core user identity (firstName, lastName, email, and locale) can only be done in the user's primary account, and only by a qualified admin in that primary account. A primary account is the user's first GetGo collaboration product account. A secondary account is one created for users who are accessing GetGo collaboration products through two different organizations (e.g., consultants, developers, freelance trainers, etc.). If a user's core identity in a secondary account must be modified, contact the Customer Service Representative for that account. Admin roles: SUPER_USER, MANAGE_USERS All qualified admins can update a user's admin status, adminRoles and managedGroupKeys. Qualified admin users will have the field identityReadOnly = false in the Get User response. You can view users' accounts in the Get User or Get All Users responses. Users have a single organizerKey across all accounts. NOTE: You cannot create a user with an admin or manager role if that user has has AdminAccess set to false. This is generally an internal-only setting and should not impact outside developers. All values must be valid and the user initiating the call must have adequate permissions to make this call.

firstName string User's first name

adminRoles role list The admin roles, if any, assigned to this user for this account.
managedGroupKeys integer The groups this user is enabled to manage.
licenseKeys integer The licenses this user is being assigned to.
groupKey integer The group this user is assigned to as a member.

subject string Subject line for a user welcome email
text string Content of the user welcome email.

Status Codes

Status Code description
400 Bad Request Users are required and must have a role assigned, the user array contains more than 100 items, any array contains a null value; email is required, cannot exceed 128 characters, and must be valid; firstName and lastName are required, must be valid strings, and cannot exceed 32 characters; locale must be valid; email subject cannot contain illegal characters or exceed 150 characters; email text cannot exceed 2000 characters.

post.description:
To create a new group, perform a POST operation on /groups. The request is a group object that must contain the group name. The group name must not be empty, exceed 75 characters, or contain illegal html characters. The request may contain a parent group key, if you want to create a subgroup to an already existing valid group. Note that, only one level of group nesting is allowed. So, a parent group can have multiple children, but cannot have grandchildren. Similarly, a child group can have a single parent, but cannot have a grandfather. The response is the group key. The example request below creates the child group Group ABC in the parent group "555" with the groupKey 777. Roles: SUPER_USER, MANAGE_USERS

Request Parameters

field data type description
name string A name for the new group
parentKey string Optional - the group identifier of the parent group

Status Codes

Status Code description
400 Bad Request Name is required; Name cannot exceed 75 characters; Name is invalid
409 Conflict Name conflict, already exists in account
422 Unprocessable Entity Groups cannot exceed 1000 in account; Parent group is already a sub-group. Only one level group nesting is allowed
507 Insufficient Storage capacity.exceeded.group

The image size must not exceed 10 KB. This method is available only for the GoToMeeting product. This operation can be completed using either a POST or PUT operation. Roles: SUPER_USER

Status Code description
400 Bad Request Name is required; Name cannot exceed 75 characters; Name is invalid
409 Conflict Name conflict, already exists in account
422 Unprocessable Entity Groups cannot exceed 1000 in account; Parent group is already a sub-group. Only one level group nesting is allowed
507 Insufficient Storage capacity.exceeded.group

Status Code description
